🔐 Part 1 — Create a Security Group for EFS:
          Step 1 — Navigate:
            Go to AWS Console → EC2 ->  In the left panel → Network & Security → Security Groups ->   Click "Create Security Group"
          Step 2 — Configure:
                  ------------------------------------
                  Setting	  Value
                  Name	    EFS-Demo
                  ------------------------------------
                  Click "Create Security Group" ✅
======================================================================================================================
📁 Part 2 — Create EFS File System:
            Step 1 —  Go to AWS Console → Search EFS
                      Click "File Systems" → Click "Create File System"
            Step 2 — Configure:  Leave Name empty
                      Select Default VPC    ->   Click "Customize"
            Step 3 — File System Settings: Leave all settings as default ->  Click Next
            Step 4 — Network Settings: ->Under Network Access → Mount Targets
                    For each Availability Zone, change the Security Group:
                      -------------------------------------------
                      Availability     Zone	Security Group
                      ap-south-1a	      EFS-Demo
                      ap-south-1b	      EFS-Demo
                      ap-south-1c	      EFS-Demo
                      -------------------------------------------
                    Click Next
            Step 5 — File System Policy:   Leave as default   ->   Click Next
            Step 6 — Review & Create: Review all settings  ->      Click "Create" ✅
            💡 EFS File System is now created and available across all 3 Availability Zones
=======================================================================================================================
🖥️ Part 3 — Launch EC2 Instance A (AZ: ap-south-1a):
          Step 1 — Navigate: Go to EC2 → Click "Launch Instance"
          Step 2 — Configure Instance:
                    --------------------------
                    Name	          EFS-InstanceA
                    OS	            Amazon Linux 2
                    Instance Type	    t2.micro
                    ----------------------------------------
                    Key Pair	Proceed without Key Pair
          Step 3 — Network Settings (Important):  Click "Edit" in Network Settings
                    Configure:
                    Setting	    Value
                    VPC	        Default VPC
                    Subnet	    ap-south-1a
          Step 4 — Configure Storage & EFS:  Scroll down to "Configure Storage" -> Select EFS
                  Click "Add Shared File System"
                  ----------------------------------------
                  Setting	          Value
                  File System	      Select the EFS created above
                  Mount Point	      /mnt/efs/fs1
                  ----------------------------------------
                  Click "Launch Instance" ✅
