🔗 Part 5 — Verify EFS Shared Storage:
            Step 1 — Connect to Instance A:  Go to EC2 → Instances
                    Select EFS-InstanceA → Click "Connect"
                    Click "Connect" in EC2 Instance Connect tab
            Step 2 — Check & Create File on Instance A:
                    # Check if EFS mount is empty
                    ls /mnt/efs/fs1
                    
                    # Create a new file
                    echo "hello world" > /mnt/efs/fs1/hello.txt
                    
                    # Verify the file is created
                    cat /mnt/efs/fs1/hello.txt
                Result:  hello world ✅
==================================================================================================================
